programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E1
programme.desc: June 1944. The Japanese are in retreat across the Pacific. Now, at the island of Saipan, they face a pivotal battle. If they lose, a deadly new American weapon - the B-29 long-range bomber - will be within range of Japan for the first time. But the Empire believes a mighty weapon of its own will win the battle - a deep-rooted tradition of aggression and sacrifice in battle. Can the Japanese warrior mindset prevail?

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E7
programme.desc: Afzal Kahn gives his team a project that could be their toughest challenge to date - to create a Jeep that is bigger and better than any other. They also have to make it a success in the USA, where the Jeep is held in very high esteem. The job must also be completed in time for the new Jeep to launch in a Hollywood showroom that Khan has specially booked for the occasion.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E8
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are off to Derbyshire to rescue a 48 year old Italian supercar: a 1971 Lamborghini Espada. This remarkable car belongs to lifelong petrol head Ged who bought the car in 1977 for #4000 however when it eventually broke down Ged's aim of one day restoring it to its former glory ground to a halt when serious health issues got in the way. Will the boys from Car SOS be able to make Ged's dream come true?

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E8
programme.desc: The rule-breaking and revolutionary Nissan GT-R competes with the big boys from the supercar world using a combination of cutting-edge aerodynamics, hi-tech engineering and a handcrafted V6 engine. It's one of the most affordable supercars on the road – mass produced on a production line in Nissan's Tochigi mega factory.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E1
programme.desc: MIA CBP target a passenger with frequent trips to Colombia and after further questioning they suspect he could be smuggling narcotics internally. Officers search cargo for narcotics staying one step ahead of the cartel. At JFK, HSI conducts a controlled delivery of ecstasy on Wall Street that was intercepted at the mail facility and at LAX two passengers are questioned about their visits. For one their past drug use comes back to haunt them.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E2
programme.desc: To uncover Turkey's hidden gems, Digital Nomad and travel enthusiast Andrew Evans heads to Western Anatolia and the Aegean Region. Following the same ancient trade routes trodden by oriental trade and spice merchants thousands of years ago, he finds a treasure trove of ancient wonders. From mysterious mountain top statues to some of the most pristine Roman remains in the world, Andrew uncovers the secrets of ancient Turkey.

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E5

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E6

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E5

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S1E6

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5 Compilations E5

Some of the best fishermen from Gloucester head south for the winter for a shot at the oceans most lucrative prey, bluefin tuna. When they arrive in Southern waters they quickly learn Southern hospitality is dead. The local boys let them Yankees know they are not welcome. All this tension leads to fierce rivalries with explosive results.

programme.desc: A study of the methods used by Italian dictator Benito Mussolini to rise to power and turn Italy into the first fascist state. A master of propaganda, he dubbed himself 'Il Duce' (the leader) and delivered bombastic speeches in which he idealized a fascist culture and promised to return Italy to the grandeur of Ancient Rome. Instead he created a one-party dictatorship and kept his grip on power for two long decades.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E9
programme.desc: An expedition searches for the iconic wrecks of the Battle of the Pacific, including the ship that delivered the Hiroshima bomb, USS Indianapolis.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E7
programme.desc: Police rush to handle a rare incident on a domestic flight: something suspicious in a Serbian citizen's bag. Agents find liquid cocaine disguised in drink bottles in another man's bag. A passenger without luggage reappears carrying a suitcase and agents rush to investigate. Counterfeit cash is uncovered in the mail facility.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E9
programme.desc: Australian hippy, Mark O'Brien is dissatisfied with life. He joins an ashram in India, lead by the infamous guru Osho, looking for enlightenment. But when a fellow disciple encourages Mark to join her in a plan to smuggle an exotic form of hash to Amsterdam, it sets of a chain of events that leads him to a very different commune; the notorious Yawanda Central Prison.

programme.title: India's Mega Kitchens S1E3
programme.desc: Watch as a sacred mega kitchen gears up to feed over 100,000 devotees in a single day for the annual festival of Lakshadeepotsava in the temple town of Dharmasthala.

programme.title: Japan: Between Earth And Sky E1
programme.desc: Japan, Land of the Rising Sun, with its panoramas forged by volcanoes and tradition, is a mighty international economic power. In the far north of the country, Hokkaido, one of the four large islands making up the archipelago, the ancient and sacred land of the Ainu people, is a vast natural paradise. This journey over the four seasons of the year, between earth and sky, volcanoes and clear lakes, tells the unique story of people who live at one with nature.

programme.title: Nasca Lines: Unlocking The Secrets
programme.desc: As Peruvian archeologists along the site of the famed Nasca Lines employed hi-tech drones to look for signs of looting and encroachment, they were surprised to discover new designs made by an older Paracas culture - originating before the time of Christ. New footage expands on these Paracas geoglyph discoveries even further, diving deeper to explore the theory of whether these glyphs were meant to glow under the light of a full moon.

programme.title: Egypt With The World's Greatest Explorer E3
programme.desc: After weeks of adventure Ran and Joe have finally reached the end of their journey, to the south is the border with Sudan. In this episode, Joe skirts the crocodile infested waters of Lake Nasser and tries his hand at sailing a traditional Egyptian Felucca. Finally, Ran and Joe say goodbye to this incredible country and its lifeblood, the River Nile, just as Ran did half a century before.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E3
programme.desc: It's trapping season and frontiersman Colbert must get to work. Selling beaver pelts in town will provide him with the bulk of the money to pay the taxes on his land and purchase small items that he cannot get from the swamp. Hunter-gatherer Matt tries hunting rabbits with his new homemade bow and arrow. If he cannot get a source of protein to store for the winter he will need to leave in search of a new shelter.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5 Compilations E6
programme.desc: Tuna fishing in the Outer Banks is anything but easy. Our Captains put their lives on the line every single day in the sheer hope of putting a bluefin on the deck. But before they make it back to the docks they have to contend with everything from rogue waves, shifting tides and the always-treacherous inlet. In this episode we count down the top 20 close calls from North Carolinas most dangerous fishery.

programme.title: Mega Air E6
programme.desc: Before lights out to start the Formula 1 season in Australia, Mega Air gets rare access behind the scenes at F1 team Haas as they rush to pack tonnes of cars and gear for air freighting. We roar back into Formula 1's past as former world champion Kimi Raikkonen's car flies to the Middle East and life-saving, temperature-controlled pharmaceuticals are given an almighty battering by the elements on a 6000 mile to Singapore.

programme.desc: In all societies, the dead command respect, their lives commemorated and their remains treated with reverence, but not everyone deals with the dead in the same way. In Madagascar, the dead are exhumed, so they can commune with the living.

Once dropped off, Bear and Rob must navigate a stretch of jagged ice fields, deep moulins, and deep crevasses. Without food or supplies to make shelter, their mission is to find an airdropped emergency cache- without it, there's no way they can survive the frigid night!

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E5
programme.desc: Next up, Greer catches up with New Zealand travel consultant Dani in the City of Sails. The duo hit the asphalt on a Harley Davidson tour, board a seaplane to Waiheke Island to visit Mudbrick Winery and much more in just 48 hours, including an adrenaline-fuelled jump off Sky Tower!

programme.title: 48 Hrs Destination S1E6
programme.desc: Greer's next whirlwind trip takes her to glittering Dubai, where she teams up with fellow travel consultant Samiera to experience everything this larger-than-life city has to offer, from four-wheel driving in the desert to being pampered in a luxurious Turkish spa. How much decadence can a girl take?

programme.title: Supercar Megabuild S1E8
programme.desc: Ralph and Ranen source a Chevrolet Camaro and adapt it for the UK market. It must cater for the growing appetite for these powerful American vehicles, but also handle the narrow winding roads in Britain, and have a more of a European styling package. With the help of “Muscle Car Joe” and Craig and Matthew Dean, the reimagined vehicle must be ready to be unveiled at Kahn's design showroom.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E9
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz travel to Jersey in the Channel Islands to take on a 1972 Ford Escort Mexico. Owner Gary has been recovering from a horrific spell of ill health, having been struck down with both blood cancer and tuberculosis, and his family hope that his restored classic will give him a new lease of life. Once the boys get the car back to the workshop they quickly realise that not one single part of the car is salvageable.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E1
programme.desc: China is the world's oldest living civilization. But as the nation modernizes, there's a new thirst to rediscover its roots. Historian Sam Willis unravels how Chinese fascination with the sky has influenced peoples and cities from the past to the present, creating a lasting understanding of the relationship between heaven and earth.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E6
programme.desc: CBP MIA finds a package of ecstasy in the mail; HSI conducts a controlled delivery leading to a stakeout and arrest. CBP at LAX monitor travelers arriving for a popular music festival where there is known drug use. CBP JFK searches a passenger with possible connections to known drug dealers. After poking holes through his story, officers decide to take him for an x-ray to find out the truth once and for all.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E7
programme.desc: Plantation pioneers of the 19th century in Malaysia designed homes for comfort and status in the midst of jungles and sprawling farms. From strategic bases close to thriving access points like Penang to rural riverine frontiers in Perak, these quintessential bungalows retain the charm and sense of sanctuary they were first built for.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E8
programme.desc: There is an obvious contrast between the architectural legacy of colonial houses and the Malay vernacular homes built to provide respite from the tropical heat. While the former escaped to the cool hills bringing with them the styles and influences of their motherland, the latter adopted the techniques of time-tested traditional village homes.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E1
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent. It's a journey of a lifetime for the unlikely duo as they traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Meeting with local historian Chen Ban, they trace the footsteps of Hakka pioneers along a series of mountain trails that formed the backbone of their livelihood, transporting commodities and goods. Travelling further south, they get their hands dirty and learn how camphor, one of Taiwan's treasures is traditionally extracted. The duo also learn more about a tea that was created by the Hakka, that embodies the very spirit of what it means to be part of a ethnicity that were once outcasts.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E2
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison is teaming up with Natalie Pickles, host and model of British and Taiwanese descent, to explore and understand the relationship of Hakka food and their traditional lifestyle. The unlikely duo traverse across Taiwan's north-western hinterlands, along a 150 km stretch of highway known as the Romantic Route 3. Along the way, Julian and Natalie meet unique characters and learn that the heart of Hakka cuisine stemmed from their traditional way of living.

programme.title: Hakka Renaissance E3
programme.desc: Historian anthropologist Julian Davison and host-model Natalie Pickles dive head in to Hakka culture by joining a Hakka Opera troupe on stage as they conclude their journey on the Taiwan Romantic Route 3. To get their performance up to scratch, our unlikely duo must first understand the basics of Hakka culture. The pair meet Professor Zheng Rom Shing to understand how Hakka opera's roots began with tea picking, before taking pronunciation lessons with a group of elementary school children. Hakka arts revolves around the environment and community.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E2
programme.desc: Explore two different sides to China's fashion industry. JNBY is the international brand making waves in the fashion scene. In their factories, rolls of fabric are processed on an industrial scale. Hanyi's Master Cheongsam maker has been perfecting his craft for 80 years, and his shop is the oldest on Shanghai's Changle Street. Here, he transforms silk into tailored and embroidered Cheongsam.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E7
programme.desc: Whilst renovating their garage, Steve and wife Marie never dreamt that they would find a World War Two bunker hidden underneath their garden. They decide to revolutionise the damp and dark space into a home office. Steve has devised an ingenious motorised lift that will lift the roof and let in light. Better still when the bunker is not in use the roof goes down and they keep full use of the garden and you'd never know what lies beneath.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E7
programme.desc: Plantation pioneers of the 19th century in Malaysia designed homes for comfort and status in the midst of jungles and sprawling farms. From strategic bases close to thriving access points like Penang to rural riverine frontiers in Perak, these quintessential bungalows retain the charm and sense of sanctuary they were first built for.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E8
programme.desc: There is an obvious contrast between the architectural legacy of colonial houses and the Malay vernacular homes built to provide respite from the tropical heat. While the former escaped to the cool hills bringing with them the styles and influences of their motherland, the latter adopted the techniques of time-tested traditional village homes.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E2
programme.desc: The beautiful cathedral of La Sagrada Familia in Barcelona, Spain has been under construction for 130 years, yet it's still not finished. Now, a team of experts is rushing to complete this masterpiece in just thirteen years. To finish this church will take not just innovation and devotion, but the most advanced technology, hard-hat construction, and the fine-grained discipline of ancient craft.

programme.title: Dive Detectives E6
programme.desc: The Fletchers penetrate the wrecks of the Hamilton and the Scourge to find out why they sank and why so many lives were lost.

programme.title: Tom's Istanbul Delight E2
programme.desc: Tom pays a visit to the multi-cultural backstreet district of Balat. His guides take him around this old neighbourhood, where it seems that time itself has stopped, to discover the magical chemistry of Turkish food that turns basic ingredients into tasty treats. After seeing some unusual ingredients and techniques, Tom returns to his kitchen and works on a marinated-preserved yoghurt ball dish.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E15
programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. People dressed in vibrant clothes, environment filled with all sorts of food aromas, Medhaghat was a perfect destination for some gala time. Pablo fished, cooked and gorged on some exceptional food with the Bodos.

programme.title: Pizza In Parma E4
programme.desc: The boys leave the Basque Country and head north into the Bordeaux region of France where they taste wine. Then, reaching the rugby town of Agen, they feed a team of hungry rugby players after their most important game of the season.

programme.title: Pizza In Parma E5
programme.desc: The boys head to Monaco where Smokey Pete puts his wheels in motion on the world's most famous Grand Prix track, and then they finally reach Italy and a town with a special connection to Wales.

programme.title: Pizza In Parma E6
programme.desc: The boys head to Rome to visit one of the hottest pizzerias in the capital and then on to Napoli, the home of pizza making, where they're treated to a feast like no other.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E10
programme.desc: Let's travel to the cloudy forests of Chiapas near the border with Guatemala where Peter explores a state with the highest indigenous population in Mexico and with it, some of the most interesting food yet.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E13
programme.desc: David meets his buddy Gianluca, who invites him to his families hometown of San Gregorio Armeno, a small town 90 minutes outside Naples. For five days straight, David, Gianluca and his family eat drink and celebrate family tradition, making tomato sauce, and hunting for truffles.

programme.title: United Plates Of America E1
programme.desc: California has one of the largest populations of Japanese people in America. Their life here and their transition into American culture hasn't been a smooth one. In this episode we uncover their trials, resilience and delicious healthy food.

programme.title: My Pacific Quest E2
programme.desc: Adventurer Ellis Emmett reaches the Kingdom of Tonga, the first stop on his ambitious Pacific sailing quest. Ellis befriends a local named Lofi, and the two set sail for the isolated island of Tofua. Along the way they explore a newly formed volcanic island, navigate treacherous coral reefs, and must hunt for their dinner.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E4
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchins visit the Chinese province of Yunnan, which contains the largest ethnic diversity in China. 25 minority groups live in the province, and the brothers visit the National Ethnic Minorities Park to learn about and hopefully understand these cultures. To further immerse themselves, they also explore native villages and take part in games, ceremonies and festivals.

programme.title: Taiwan: Island Of Fish E6
programme.desc: As demand for fish is outstripping supply, aquaculture is going mainstream. Liu Tian raises fish not to make money but to make people healthier. Entrepreneur Michael Lai has spent years searching for the right material for replacement corneas. He believes the scales from the Taiwan tilapia may hold the answer. Can these innovators propel their vision from concept to reality?

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E1
programme.sub-title: What The Region Is Famous For
programme.desc: Chef and Restaurateur Peter Kuruvita begins a new culinary adventure in the extraordinary region of Margaret River; discovering a world of food, wine and colourful characters along the way.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E2
programme.desc: Peter continues his journey throughout Margaret River meeting extraordinary artisanal producers of the region and using their ingredients in a host of delicious dishes.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E3
programme.desc: Peter gains a greater understanding of bush foods as he forages with the region's traditional owners.

After lending a hand at a vineyard, and learning what makes these grapes so highly prized, he will risk it all to discover the local secret of what makes this China's largest grape growing region. He also will find the top chefs to teach him three of his favourite Chinese dishes and make a Turpan inspired feast to celebrate the end of harvest.

programme.desc: In this episode, Jamie is at his last stop on the silk road journey, Urumqi, the capital of Xinjiang. programme.title: Bangkok Airport E4
programme.desc: It is Valentine's Day at the airport. Romance blossoms for immigration officers Bert and Nat, Captain Jack shares the secrets of a successful marriage and there are free hugs for every passenger. Justin jets in for cosmetic surgery to perk up his love life, Nathan introduces his parents to his new Thai boyfriend and a Swiss traveler flies to Thailand to meet his internet girlfriend.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: Exploring Malaysia S2E1
programme.desc: In this episode, world-record-breaking sailor Jesse Martin embarks on an inspirational nautical adventure along Malaysia Borneo's north-eastern coast. Exploring a region rich in seafaring cultures, he immerses himself in the lives of the sailors, sea gypsies, fishermen and marine conservationists who share his passion for life on the open sea.

programme.title: Miguel's Tropical Kitchen E13
programme.desc: In this episode of Miguel's Tropical Kitchen our Spanish chef mixes tropical produce with global cuisine, dishing up an exotic Asian beef salad, Italian angel hair pasta with scallops, and a beautiful French Pineapple Tarte Tatin.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E1
programme.desc: Miguel visits one of New Zealand's biggest mussel men and they feast on the traditional fresh seafood cuisine together. Then Miguel rises to the challenge of a dinner party where each guest sets down their own dietary requirement! He decides on cooking Quinoa Raviolo with tomato salsa. Whether it is well-prepared or not, it is the guests' call.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E3
programme.desc: Explore the waterways of China, home to both sleek, snazzy yachts and lovingly hand-crafted dragon-boats. We uncover the marvels of engineering behind the yachts at Sino-Eagle, and watch master craftsmen painstakingly build traditional dragon-boats.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E4
programme.desc: Relive childhood dreams and delve into the world of traditional and modern toys, from the complex electronic flying RC Helicopters to simple paper kites. See the inner workings of a Syma factory, and then head to the kite capital of the world to learn how art, science and devotion to one's craft brings life to intricate kites.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E5
programme.desc: Explore the changing landscape of music in China, as old and new sounds merge. Deep inside the Pearl River Piano factory, planks of wood are transformed with great precision into intricate instruments, and we see how all the various parts come together. Over at the Shanghai Number 1 Musical Instruments Factory, watch as a master technician guides his apprentices on how to make the perfect Guzheng.

programme.title: Two Tales Of China E6
programme.desc: Noodles are a beloved staple of Chinse cuisine, from modern packets of instant noodles to traditional shops selling hand-made noodles. Head into the depths of the Master Kong factory in Tianjin, which produces noodles for the whole country. Then to Sichuan, where Zhongjiang noodles have been handmade since the Song Dynasty.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E1
programme.desc: Rob and Leon arrive on the edge of the Gobi Desert and pick up last minute supplies for their 6-month trip.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E2
programme.desc: In Jining, Rob's foot is proven all right by an x-ray. But, not long after that, the pair suffer diarrhea from some ill-prepared food.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E9
programme.desc: Sara strolls down memory lane and ranks her top five moments in Australia. From Melbourne, Darwin to Broome and Victoria, she prepares unforgettable delicacies like lamp chop and octopus bashing. Also, she savors unique cuisines like pizza made by alfresco oven. Other than cooking, Sara spends time with a group of kangaroos feeding on grass and also witnesses an alligator hunting for food.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E2
programme.desc: Miguel discovers that milking from a salmon is the secret to create bacon and egg twist! And forget fancy restaurants, Miguel hits the streets to check out ready-to-eat food - 'meals on wheels'. From the Veggie Patch to the pan, Miguel learns the craft and simplicity of the ultimate pumpkin soup and he witnesses a single cocoa bean turning from chocolate to a five-star dessert.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E3
programme.desc: Miguel goes to Leaning Oak Dairy to learn how to milk a goat and produce the creamiest goat cheese. Wrapping up his rustic experience in the dairy, he prepares a classic cuisine - Bubble & Squeak. Then, he visits the Queen of the rice paper roll. The queen gets not only attitude, but also all the tips for the best rolls in town. Plus, Miguel learns to cook pasta to the best.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E4
programme.desc: Miguel samples the extra virgin olive oil in a top-notch factory. Other than food, Miguel shares his outlook on life and defines his interpretation of success. Then, he prepares a delectable feast for his family to show his affection before showcasing an array of dishes, including rolled chicken stuffed with chorizo & pistachio and crispy skin kingfish with tomato salsa & gazpacho.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E5
programme.desc: Throughout history, mankind has been on a mad-dash to satisfy our prodigious sweet tooth and consume vital energy. Along the way sugar helped build empires and even fueled the Industrial Revolution. From the time sugarcane was first refined in India, to our newest high-tech candy factories, we've been developing newer and better delivery systems for the taste we can't live without.

programme.title: Escape To Costa Rica E2
programme.desc: This week, Gaia goes whitewater rafting down Costa Rica's most spectacular river to a remote eco-lodge, to meet the people who fought to save the river from being dammed – then visits the largest hydrodam in central America. She treks into the exclusion zone of an active volcano, and takes a dip in a hot spring, to understand how Costa Ricans have harnessed one of nature's most destructive forces. And on the stunning Pacific coast, she helps build artificial reefs made from the most unlikely recycling materials.

programme.title: Straight To The Source: Korean Food E3
programme.desc: To begin their tour of discovering Korea's mastery of fermentation, Ricky leads Todd to a tiny village to go behind-the-scenes with kimchi, a Korean national dish, before moving to Andong to sample aged-kimchi. Next they are in Jincheon-gun to check out a popular Korean beverage called makgeolli. At last, the pair comes up with their own makgeolli and kimchi-inspired dish with lobster.

programme.title: Straight To The Source: Korean Food E4
programme.desc: This time Todd and Ricky are on a mission to discover how ginseng doubles as a health food and a chef's best-kept secret. First, they are in Insadong, Seoul to sample samgyetang, the ginseng chicken soup. After they try harvesting ginseng in Cheongwon-gun and visit a ginseng festival in Geumsan-gun, they reward themselves by creating their own ginseng-inspired dish in their kitchen.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E4
programme.desc: Living Color is commissioned to create the centerpiece for a beach home on Grand Cayman Island. They envision a giant aquarium featuring marine life of the surrounding waters, but removing ornamental fish from Cayman waters is illegal. Mat Roy places resident fish expert Francis at the helm. With his encyclopedic knowledge of fish, this job should be a breeze.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E3
programme.desc: On the map, Rob and Leon find out that sneaking through a tunnel will save them three days of walking, but they must walk the 18km at night to avoid suspicion.

Destination Extreme follows these athletes as they discover the ultimate location and explain why that mountain range, ocean swell, or valley floor, can't compare to anywhere else in the world.

programme.title: Destination Extreme E8
programme.desc: Destination Extreme is a Hi Def exploration of the planet's most exciting action sports destinations, told by the athletes that make these hotspots their playground. Destination Extreme follows these athletes as they discover the ultimate location and explain why that mountain range, ocean swell, or valley floor, can't compare to anywhere else in the world.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E5
programme.desc: What is it like to be stranded at Bangkok Airport? Darren from London has his passport stolen and British-Afghan veteran John is down to his last 20 pence till the tourist police step in. A panic attack grounds a young Aussie tourist in departures, a Swedish backpacker is savaged by a dog, and concern grows for the safety of a young Indian traveler.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E15
programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. People dressed in vibrant clothes, environment filled with all sorts of food aromas, Medhaghat was a perfect destination for some gala time. Pablo fished, cooked and gorged on some exceptional food with the Bodos.

programme.title: Exploring Malaysia S2E2
programme.desc: Hidden beneath the surface of a remote corner of Malaysia Borneo lies a parallel universe of such elemental beauty, mystery and strangeness that it feels like it belongs on another planet. Naturalist Nick Baker embarks on a subterranean adventure into the magnificent cave systems of Sarawak to discover how the local people and wildlife have adapted to a landscape that is riddled with holes.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E3
programme.desc: Miguel goes to Leaning Oak Dairy to learn how to milk a goat and produce the creamiest goat cheese. Wrapping up his rustic experience in the dairy, he prepares a classic cuisine - Bubble & Squeak. Then, he visits the Queen of the rice paper roll. The queen gets not only attitude, but also all the tips for the best rolls in town. Plus, Miguel learns to cook pasta to the best.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E4
programme.desc: Miguel samples the extra virgin olive oil in a top-notch factory. Other than food, Miguel shares his outlook on life and defines his interpretation of success. Then, he prepares a delectable feast for his family to show his affection before showcasing an array of dishes, including rolled chicken stuffed with chorizo & pistachio and crispy skin kingfish with tomato salsa & gazpacho.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E4
programme.desc: Peter uncovers a community of farmers that are focussing on sustainability before using these amazing ingredients to cook up a storm in his coastal kitchen.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E5
programme.desc: Peter indulges his passion for seafood by diving for abalone, cooking up some local crayfish and curing trout with a delicious Margaret River gin.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita Coastal Kitchen S2E6
programme.desc: Peter completes his tour of Margaret River hosting a spectacular Beachside BBQ as part of the Gourmet Escape.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S1E2
programme.desc: Miguel discovers that milking from a salmon is the secret to create bacon and egg twist! And forget fancy restaurants, Miguel hits the streets to check out ready-to-eat food - 'meals on wheels'. From the Veggie Patch to the pan, Miguel learns the craft and simplicity of the ultimate pumpkin soup and he witnesses a single cocoa bean turning from chocolate to a five-star dessert.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E3
programme.desc: On the map, Rob and Leon find out that sneaking through a tunnel will save them three days of walking, but they must walk the 18km at night to avoid suspicion.

programme.title: Walking Home From Mongolia E4
programme.desc: Rob and Leon set off in search of the famous mountain scenery of China's 20 RMB bill in Guilin. Then, Rob and Leon walk on towards Guangzhou, and while there, Leon gets heatstroke, and can barely keep himself upright.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E3
programme.desc: Recently added to the world heritage list as a cultural asset, the iconic Mt. Fuji is a well-known symbol of Japan. Every year the volcano's scenic beauty draws more and more visitors from around the world. Dedicated mountain rangers, scientists, and eco-volunteers are working hard to preserve and protect the mountain from mankind while also protecting mankind from the mountain.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E7
programme.desc: Whilst renovating their garage, Steve and wife Marie never dreamt that they would find a World War Two bunker hidden underneath their garden. They decide to revolutionise the damp and dark space into a home office. Steve has devised an ingenious motorised lift that will lift the roof and let in light. Better still when the bunker is not in use the roof goes down and they keep full use of the garden and you'd never know what lies beneath.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E5
programme.desc: What is it like to be stranded at Bangkok Airport? Darren from London has his passport stolen and British-Afghan veteran John is down to his last 20 pence till the tourist police step in. A panic attack grounds a young Aussie tourist in departures, a Swedish backpacker is savaged by a dog, and concern grows for the safety of a young Indian traveler.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E41
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys head to their third location on their Hobart Food Crawl to a small Italian style restaurant on the outskirts of the Hobart CBD. This restaurant is 20 seat and specialises in share plates, unique wines and communal dining. Up at The University of Queensland Ben and Joel make a traditional Italian dish, Cacio e Pepe, translating to ‘cheese and pepper', Joel explains a little about starches along the way.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E42
programme.desc: Rhys takes Ben down to Tom Mchugo's, an old style corner pub and hotel in the city, this will be their fourth stop on their food crawl. They kick back and enjoy a cold beer, oysters and what Rhys has announced is the best fried chicken in the south of Tassie.

programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Vita S6E13
programme.desc: David meets his buddy Gianluca, who invites him to his families hometown of San Gregorio Armeno, a small town 90 minutes outside Naples. For five days straight, David, Gianluca and his family eat drink and celebrate family tradition, making tomato sauce, and hunting for truffles.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E1
programme.desc: Like the carnival festivals of Rio and Venice, Goa marks the days before Lent with an all-out celebration: three full days of eating, drinking, and partying. David takes part in all of the festivities, including an appearance on a float in Panjim's annual Carnival kick-off parade. He ends up spending time with some Italian expats and celebrating the holiday Venetian-style.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E4
programme.desc: A full-scale invasion of escaped pets and exotic species threatens to wipe out the wildlife in Everglades National Park, and a snarling system of dams and canals is slowly strangling its fragile ecosystem. So severe is the threat that UNESCO has put the park on their list of most vulnerable locations. Now, the defenders of this World Heritage Site are fighting back – before it's too late.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E8
programme.desc: John, a tailor from London dreams of creating his own office space in the garden so he can spend more time closer to home, after the arrival of a newborn baby. Sadly, John's DIY skills might not be up to the job! So he recruits his old friend Stephen to help him design and build a tailor's studio he'll be proud to bring his clients to.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E5
programme.desc: Turpan, nicknamed the world's sweetest city, is the next leg of Jamie's culinary journey. After lending a hand at a vineyard, and learning what makes these grapes so highly prized, he will risk it all to discover the local secret of what makes this China's largest grape growing region. He also will find the top chefs to teach him three of his favourite Chinese dishes and make a Turpan inspired feast to celebrate the end of harvest.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E6
programme.desc: In this episode, Jamie is at his last stop on the silk road journey, Urumqi, the capital of Xinjiang. He will spend time with the lovely Kazakh friends in the mountains and experience an amazing array of ethnically diverse foods from Kazakh horsemeat to Uyghur baked buns. He will get an exclusive lesson in making everybody's favourite noodle dish and to top it all off, he will cook his own dishes for the most important festival in the Islamic calendar.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E6
programme.desc: An unhappy tourist tries to strangle an airport official and a Full-Moon party goes wrong for two young British girls while the English Thai boxing team flies in to fight for the world championship. As political unrest sweeps the country and threatens to close down the airport, Captain Jack, the happiest man in the immigration department, finally stops smiling.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E51
programme.desc: Ben makes an extremely quick and easy Panzanella Salad, the perfect summer dish to enjoy in the Brisbane heat. He then heads to the Huon Harvest pods at Hideaway Bay down South. Here Ben learns about their harvesting practices and their harvest by night fresher by day approach from master salmon harvester Luggsy on an extremely calm and mild night.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E52
programme.desc: Ben and the crew are back down in the Tarkine cooking a pineapple pork stir fry at base camp. In Brisbane Joel joins Ben and they put together a honey and lemon haloumi dish, as Joel explains his theory behind what the term ‘squeaky cheese' refers to. In the studio kitchen Ben uses the cheese stuffed tortellini to make an awesome bacon and pepper dish.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E16
programme.desc: A 700-year-old village of the Angami Nagas is a perfect example of a close-knit community. Pablo gets a glimpse of their community culture visiting a community house followed by a community kitchen where he devours on some exotic Naga food. What surprised Pablo the most about this tribe was their transformation from fierce headhunters to farmers.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E15
programme.desc: The village of Medhaghat in Assam- home to the Bodos, was soaked in festivities on Pablo's arrival. People dressed in vibrant clothes, environment filled with all sorts of food aromas, Medhaghat was a perfect destination for some gala time. Pablo fished, cooked and gorged on some exceptional food with the Bodos.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E2
programme.desc: Formerly a colony of Portugal, Goa still has a large Portuguese population, and nowhere is their influence more evident than in the local cuisine. David is on a mission to discover Goa's unique blend of Portuguese and Indian cultures, one dish at a time. He also learns about the Toddy Vinegar that gives many dishes their signature Goan touch.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E3
programme.desc: David heads out on a crab fishing expedition with some local fishermen in a nearby river. Afterwards, he meets up with an internationally-renowned chef Cyrus Todiwala, who takes him to the local fish market to check out what is on offer. Later, David gets a chance to explore Goa's famous beach shack culture and ventures into Calamari, a renowned seafood restaurant, to flex his culinary muscles.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E5
programme.desc: Living Colors most demanding client is Jim Prappas, the head biologist at Rainforest Cafe. This time the project is at Disney World, the tanks that decorate this highly trafficked space are in desperate need of a reef makeover. As if a two week deadline wasn't difficult enough, Jim wants the restored reef to feature molds of the highly prized coral known as Stylophora pistillata.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E1
programme.desc: We start on the tiny island of Batan, meeting a unique viper and a ubiquitous but also giant, land crab. Luzon is the main island of the Philippines. We drop in to Mindoro to see the most endangered large mammal in the Philippines, the tamaraw. The bustling capital of Manila dominates the centre of this large island but despite encroachments, huge areas of wilderness still exist. Here we meet blue tarantulas and strange forest birds. In the town of Pulilan we join a celebration that centres on the carabao, water buffalo. In the Verde Passage we join a group of photographers surveying the marine creatures of the area, from frog fish to pygmy seahorses. We also meet the people who have dedicated their lives to saving the most endangered crocodile in the world. On Palawan we find new sea creatures that charm and awe eco-tourists and take a trip along the longest navigable underground river to meet bats and swiftlets. We discover the sad recent history of the Palawan forest turtl.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn E1
programme.desc: At night, the dunes of the Arabian desert come to life with unique animals specially adapted to thrive in this hostile environment, from lizards that swim under the sand to spiders that can run ten miles per hour.

programme.title: Snake Island: Wild & Deadly
programme.desc: On a barren Australian island deadly tiger snakes survive in a place that is hostile and unforgiving. There is no fresh water or regular food. They live in the shadow of a brutal attacker that pecks their eyes out defending their offspring from the snake's ravenous hunger. Despite this they are thriving and have become giants of their kind. But why they are here and how they prosper in this desolate place has remained a mystery? until now.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E1
programme.desc: Mike travels to Austin in search of three of Texas' most amazing fish - one is so smart it can out-think the average fisherman and get away, one is so rare it's found nowhere else on the planet, and the last one is giant and secretive, requiring days of fishing - with little hope of success.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E3
programme.desc: Mike travels to London, England in search of three of the great city's most iconic fish species. One is a fearsome predator that will even devour birds, another is piscine royalty that is often known as 'The Prince of the River' and one is a sentimental favourite that has recovered from a devastating disease outbreak.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E3
programme.desc: In this episode of Animal Fight Club, nature gets nasty as the animal kingdom prepares for wild-life warfare. Using remarkable footage, gathered from the world's leading nature documentary makers; combined with stunning, 'under the skin' CGI, we reveal the strategies, techniques and weaponry used when animals fight for their bloodline and survival.

programme.title: Snake Island: Wild & Deadly
programme.desc: On a barren Australian island deadly tiger snakes survive in a place that is hostile and unforgiving. There is no fresh water or regular food. They live in the shadow of a brutal attacker that pecks their eyes out defending their offspring from the snake's ravenous hunger. Despite this they are thriving and have become giants of their kind. But why they are here and how they prosper in this desolate place has remained a mystery? until now.

programme.title: World's Weirdest S1E1
programme.desc: Take a deep dive into the realm of creepy aquatic creatures to uncover the world's most bizarre water-dwelling tenants. In this episode a fish with a transparent head shows everything it's got. A master-of-disguise octopus camouflages itself to capture prey or elude pursuit. A lizard literally walks on water and a fish walks on dry land... and that's just for starters!

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E3
programme.desc: In this episode, expect to see how a boy named Jeremy befriends his family cat called Tara, who saved him from a deadly canine attack. Also, a mother dog named Piper formed a maternal bond with her 'goat puppy' called GP, and a man loves to spoil the family's pet deer called Dillie.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E12
programme.desc: Mat Roy and his chief creative force Jose Blanco head across the country where a special celebrity client has a dream that he wants to make reality. Cesar Milan is building an elaborate retreat for dogs and their owners, aiming for a spa-like experience. He wants a koi fish pond as the meditative centerpiece of his desert oasis. Unquestionably one of Living Color's the most unique jobs.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E2
programme.desc: Moving from turtles of the Palawan coast to the unique National Marine Park at Tubbataha, to meet giants, whale sharks and manta rays. On Bohol we explore the Chocolate hills and met the man who has done more than anyone else to help the Philippine tarsier, a tiny, bug-eyed primate. We also see how people can mediate between people and wildlife as we join a snake hunting team catching and translocating a deadly Samar cobra. On Cebu we join the crowds that come to swim with whale sharks, explore the island home of the sea krait and thrill to see a pelagic thresher shark. On Mindanao we visit a family that have been caring for the endemic Philippine sailfin lizards for many years, so long in fact, that they get 160 or more turning up for breakfast. On Samal island we see the world's greatest concentration of Geoffroys Rousette fruit bats and learn of their value to local farmers. In the South of Mindanao we end with the most iconic Philippine animal of all, the majestic Philipp.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E3
programme.desc: Meet the Polygon Pack, a family of arctic wolves surviving and raising young in amidst the polygon ponds of the high arctic.

programme.title: Monster Constrictors
programme.desc: They are the big, the bold and arguably the most majestic of the snake world? super sleuths, silent yet deadly predators, that squeeze the life out of their victims. Pythons are nature's Monster Constrictors. Rather than pack the potent punch of a venom payload, constrictors use stealth and muscle power alone to subdue and extinguish their unwary prey. While some target the small and weak, others take on David and Goliath battles for the sake of a decent feed? Don't be fooled by their docile appearance - or the fact that they lack lethal fangs - these insidious killers are just as deadly as their notoriously venomous brethren. Their weapon of choice; constriction. Comparatively subtle, but no less effective. Yet some also have a tender side, with most python mothers shivering to generate warmth for their egg clutches, sheltering precious eggs in their protective coils. In Africa, they reach mega magnitudes and levels of aggression. In Florida, they have thrived to plague prop.

programme.title: Snake Island: Wild & Deadly
programme.desc: On a barren Australian island deadly tiger snakes survive in a place that is hostile and unforgiving. There is no fresh water or regular food. They live in the shadow of a brutal attacker that pecks their eyes out defending their offspring from the snake's ravenous hunger. Despite this they are thriving and have become giants of their kind. But why they are here and how they prosper in this desolate place has remained a mystery? until now.

programme.title: Frozen Islands E1
programme.desc: In the Southern Atlantic and Indian Oceans, between the latitudes of 40 and 60 degrees South, there is a scattering of tiny, inhospitable islands that are crucial to the survival of millions of marine creatures that use these islands to breed. South Georgia, Bouvet, Marion and Crozet Islands are home to some of the world's largest populations of Elephant Seals, Antarctic Fur Seals, Wandering Albatross, King and Macaroni Penguins. These creatures, superbly adapted to life in a freezing ocean need to come ashore to mate and raise their young. And where there are millions of animals there are the hunters that follow: Killer Whales.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E6
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley sees two stubborn muskoxen and a particularly wily coyote. A badly burned dog receives an innovative, if fishy, new treatment.

programme.title: Kingdom Of The White Wolf E1
programme.desc: Ronan Donovan, our expert guide and National Geographic photographer, takes the audience on an intimate exploration of the Arctic during the endless day of the summer months, giving insight to the unexpected abundance of the 'Garden of the Arctic' in Wolf Valley as he attempts to embed with a wolf family pack.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn E2
programme.desc: At night, the dunes of the Arabian desert come to life with unique animals specially adapted to thrive in this hostile environment, from lizards that swim under the sand to spiders that can run ten miles per hour.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E3
programme.desc: After the murder of one of their own, the Makulu Pack of Wild Dogs looks to a new leader for salvation. The Western Pride is exiled to the fringes the Kingdom as they fight to protect their cubs from enemies on all sides. And as the marauding hyena clan commits the cruelest of acts, their ferocious commander Mmamotse reveals her soft side as she swells her ranks and trains a new army.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E2
programme.desc: Mike's in Taiwan to search for three species of fish. One fish is a drain dwelling monster that originally escaped from fish farms, another is a mysterious visitor from the open seas that makes fleeting visits to the city via a watery highway and the final challenge is a true monster, who's reputation includes biting its prey clean in half and having teeth like a shark.

programme.title: Fish My City With Mike Iaconelli E4
programme.desc: Doubling down, Mike challenges himself to catching six different species of fish; three exotic species that have all travelled a long way to make themselves at home in Miami's fresh-water canals, and three salt-water classics including the fastest and one of the oldest fish living today.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E3 !
programme.sub-title: There's A Snake In The Fridge
programme.desc: Snakes in the City is a documentary-style reality TV series centering on the daily life of snake rescuers, Simon Keys, and his herpetologist girlfriend, Siouxsie Gillett in the coastal city of Durban, South Africa. This once was a tropical jungle teaming with spitting cobras, green mambas, black mambas, pythons, night adders, bush snakes and boomslangs: it's their territory and humans built a city right on top of it. Today, the jungle may be gone, but the snakes sure ain't! Summer is here and the heat and humidity bring them out of hiding, into direct conflict with the 3.5 million inhabitants of this city. There is a snake in nearly ever home so Simon and Siouxsie, experts in animal behavior, hunt down and capture by hand, the world's most dangerous and venomous snakes that emerge every summer. They then release these problem snakes back in the wild away from humans. Every call out is a chance to save a snake's life and with this being his busiest time of year, they're on cal.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S6E4
programme.desc: Simon and Sioux nearly get bitten catching and releasing mating Boomslangs. Teamwork is everything, but sometimes they split up to help all the snakes.

programme.title: Frozen Islands E1
programme.desc: In the Southern Atlantic and Indian Oceans, between the latitudes of 40 and 60 degrees South, there is a scattering of tiny, inhospitable islands that are crucial to the survival of millions of marine creatures that use these islands to breed. South Georgia, Bouvet, Marion and Crozet Islands are home to some of the world's largest populations of Elephant Seals, Antarctic Fur Seals, Wandering Albatross, King and Macaroni Penguins. These creatures, superbly adapted to life in a freezing ocean need to come ashore to mate and raise their young. And where there are millions of animals there are the hunters that follow: Killer Whales.

programme.title: The Naked Superhero
programme.desc: Looks aren't everything. Despite its appearance, the Naked Molerat should be envied. It lives to a very old age, never gets sick, and is practically impervious to pain. Scientists want to know why. In the quest to combat age-related illness - and even ageing itself - researchers around the world are searching for the Methuselah gene in this remarkable rodent to find cures for humans.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E7

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E3
programme.desc: In this episode, expect to see how a boy named Jeremy befriends his family cat called Tara, who saved him from a deadly canine attack. Also, a mother dog named Piper formed a maternal bond with her 'goat puppy' called GP, and a man loves to spoil the family's pet deer called Dillie.

programme.title: Secrets Of The Zoo S1E1
programme.desc: The zoo doctors go into hero mode, rescuing 16 macaws from a hoarding situation in Alabama, taking cheetah Emmet into a shoulder surgery that has never been attempted on his species before. At the Wilds conservation park, the doctors perform pregnancy tests on rare mares, while trying to find the medical cause of why a horse separated from the herd. Twin polar bear cubs, Niva and Nuniq, test their swimming skills in the shallow pool, before taking a leap of faith off the deep end and flamingo, Haleakala, shows love and appreciation for her keepers treating her stiff legs.

programme.title: Climbing Redwood Giants: Life In The Sky
programme.desc: Climbing Redwood Giants- Life in the Sky tells the story of the worlds tallest living trees. Humboldt State Universitys Steve Sillett, the first researcher to explore the redwood canopy, is obsessed with monster redwoods. As Sillett investigates redwoods up in their towering crowns, National Geographic Photographer Jim Balog photographs every inch of these fascinating trees.

programme.title: Tree Climbing Lions
programme.desc: Big cat biologist Alexander Braczkowski is on a mission. He's got 90 days to count lions in Uganda and learn how the population is doing. But these aren't ordinary lions. The prides in Queen Elizabeth National Park spend most of their lives up in the trees, a rare and mysterious behavior unique to this part of Africa. On his journey, he'll witness mothers battling the odds to raise cubs through their first year of life, and the threats tree climbing lions face as the human population expands. Alex's experience will become more personal than he could have imagined, and he'll learn that saving lions can be about much more than counting cats.

Rough Cut
programme.desc: Saat seorang bintang film menyewa sesosok gangster untuk menjadi lawan mainnya demi menghindari skandal setelah menghajar aktor lainnya hingga nyaris tewas, ia tak menyangka akan menghadapi sosok nan mematikan.

programme.title: The Target
programme.desc: Seorang dokter UGD bekerjasama dengan target pembunuhan dalam pengejaran selama 36 jam untuk menyelamatkan istrinya yang hamil. Mereka mengungkap korupsi yang telah lama menjangkiti departemen kepolisian.

programme.title: The Mayor
programme.desc: Byeon Jong-gu, walikota Seoul, mencalonkan diri sebagai presiden. Ia menggunakan segala cara untuk menyembunyikan rahasia-rahasia tergelapnya dari publik yang menyukainya.

programme.title: Countdown
programme.desc: Seorang penagih utang menderita kanker hati dan harus mendapatkan transplantasi hati dalam sepuluh hari. Seorang penipu bersedia mendonorkan hatinya jika ia bisa melacak pria yang memasukkannya ke dalam penjara.

programme.title: Love Forecast
programme.desc: Kisah kehidupan cinta seorang reporter cuaca nan elegan, Hyun-woo, yang menjalin hubungan dengan tiga pria, yaitu Jun-su yang setia, Hyo-bong yang canggung dan Dong-jin yang sempurna tapi sudah menikah.

programme.title: Detective K: Virtuous Widow
programme.desc: Detektif top Joseon menyelidiki serangkaian pembunuhan misterius yang berkaitan dengan konspirasi besar yang dapat menggemparkan seluruh negeri.

programme.title: I Am The King
programme.desc: Seorang pangeran yang melarikan diri bertemu dengan seorang budak yang sangat mirip dengan dirinya. Sang pangeran disangka sebagai budak dan si budak dinobatkan sebagai Raja.

programme.title: Kim Ji Young, Born 1982
programme.desc: Kim Ji-young, seorang wanita Korea berusia 30-an, tiba-tiba menunjukkan tanda-tanda dirasuki oleh sosok almarhum ibu dan kakak perempuannya setelah ia menjadi ibu rumah tangga.

programme.title: Scarlet Innocence
programme.desc: Deokee, seorang gadis dari suatu kota kecil, dicampakkan oleh seorang dosen bernama Hak-kyu yang menjalin hubungan terlarang dengannya. Delapan tahun kemudian, ia membalas dendam usai sang dosen mengalami kebutaan.

programme.title: The Outlaws
programme.desc: Untuk menjaga perdamaian, seorang detektif nan kejam dan timnya berencana untuk meringkus gangster yang paling ditakuti di Seoul.

programme.title: Hit-And-Run Squad
programme.desc: Seorang detektif polisi veteran dan seorang polisi muda bekerjasama untuk menangkap seorang pengusaha kaya raya sekaligus pembalap yang gila kecepatan dan kekuasaan.

programme.title: Dark Figure Of Crime
programme.desc: Terinspirasi dari kisah nyata, film ini menceritakan tentang sebuah pertarungan psikologis nan sengit antara seorang detektif polisi dan seorang pembunuh yang mengaku telah melakukan beberapa pembunuhan.

programme.title: The Classified File
programme.desc: Seorang detektif veteran dan sesosok peramal menjalin kerja sama yang tidak biasa untuk menyelamatkan seorang anak yang diculik sebelum terlambat.

programme.title: Sunflower
programme.desc: Seorang mantan gangster yang dibebaskan dari penjara ingin menjalani kehidupan nan tenang bersama keluarganya. Namun, niatnya terancam saat seorang politisi mencoba membongkar restoran keluarganya demi membangun mal.

programme.title: The Magician
programme.desc: Seorang pesulap muda nan berbakat jatuh cinta pada seorang putri yang bertunangan dengan mantan gurunya. Hal ini menyebabkan sebuah pertikaian sengit antara dua pesulap nan hebat.

programme.title: Shoot Me In The Heart
programme.desc: Dua pemuda bertemu di sebuah rumah sakit jiwa. Soo-myung mengalami trauma karena sang ibu bunuh diri dan Seung-min dimasukkan secara paksa ke sana meskipun ia waras. Bagaimanakah jalinan takdir mereka?

programme.title: Rough Cut
programme.desc: Saat seorang bintang film menyewa sesosok gangster untuk menjadi lawan mainnya demi menghindari skandal setelah menghajar aktor lainnya hingga nyaris tewas, ia tak menyangka akan menghadapi sosok nan mematikan.

programme.title: Sunset In My Hometown
programme.desc: Ketika seorang rapper yang kurang sukses kembali ke kampung halamannya untuk mengunjungi ayahnya yang sakit, ia bertemu kembali dengan teman-teman dan keluarganya yang ia tinggalkan dulu.

programme.title: A Day
programme.desc: Seorang dokter menyaksikan kecelakaan mobil yang melibatkan putrinya, dan pada hari yang sama secara berulang-ulang. Ia pun berjuang untuk keluar dari putaran waktu dan menyelamatkan putrinya.

programme.title: Hit-And-Run Squad

programme.title: Fatal Intuition
programme.desc: Seorang pria mencoba untuk menemukan pembunuh saudarinya dan membalas dendam dengan meminta bantuan seorang cenayang.

programme.title: The Battleship Island
programme.desc: Selama pemerintahan kolonial Jepang, sekitar 400 warga Korea diwajibkan untuk bekerja di Pulau Hashima. Ketika rahasia kelam pulau itu terungkap, para pekerja Korea berencana untuk melarikan diri.

programme.title: Kim Ji Young, Born 1982

programme.title: Sori: Voice From The Heart
programme.desc: Saat mencari putrinya yang hilang, seorang ayah menemukan sebuah satelit yang mampu mengingat suara dari seluruh dunia. Menggunakan suara putrinya sebagai suar, satelit itu membantunya melacak sang putri.
